gov.nih.nlm.meme.client
Class MEMERelaEditorKit

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.client.ClientAPI
      gov.nih.nlm.meme.client.MEMERelaEditorKit
public class MEMERelaEditorKit
extends ClientAPI

This client API is a quick and dirty implementation of "molecular actions" functionality needed for Vladimir's Rela Editor application. Aside from that use, THIS CLASS SHOULD NEVER BE USED.

To use the editor kit you will need to instantiate it by passing the constructor a valid mid services name.

There are several methods which allow the application to ask for valid sets of relationship names, relationship attributes, or sources. The purpose of these methods is to allow the application to supply a data-driven select list instead of having users enter values manually.

The remaining editor kit methods allow you to insert relationships between various different identifiers, or to make changes to known relationships that already span those identifiers. All relationships are inserted in an unreleasable state, so a changeRelationshipTBR method is supplied to allow you to make these relationships releasable.

It is wort noting that if the source or source_of_label parameters passed to the insert methods do not exist in the source_rank table but they do match the form 'NLM%' then a special private procedure is called to add that new source to source_rank with a rank equal to the NLM source. These sources will have to be more fully edited later by using the SRC Info editor

Here is an example of how to use the kit.

 import gov.nih.nlm.meme.MEMERelaEditorKit;
 import java.sql.*;
 ...

 public class Test {

   ...

   public void useEditorKit() throws MEMEException {
     String mid = "editing-db";

     // Create editor kit
     MEMERelaEditorKit editor_kit = new MEMERelaEditorKit(mid);

     // Call accessor methods
     String [] rels = editor_kit.getRelationshipNames();
     String [] relas = editor_kit.getRelationshipAttributes();
     String [] sources = editor_kit.getSources();
     String [] tobereleased = editor_kit.getTobereleased();

     // Add a new RELA to the system
     // It only gets added if it is not already there
     insertRelationshipAttribute("tradename_of","has_tradename");

     // Update a relationship using CUIs
     try {
        editor_kit.processRelationshipBetweenCUIs("C0000001","C0000002",
          "BT", "mapped_to", "NLM01", "NLM01", "F01-BAC", 12345);
     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error processing relationship (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

     // Update a relationship using atom ids
     try {
        editor_kit.processRelationshipBetweenAtoms(12345,12346,
          "BT", "mapped_to", "NLM01", "NLM01", "F01-BAC", 12345);
     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error processing relationship (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

     // Update a relationship using concept ids
     try {
        editor_kit.processRelationshipBetweenConcepts(102345,102346,
          "BT", "mapped_to", "NLM01", "NLM01", "F01-BAC", 12345);
     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error processing relationship (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

     // Insert a relationship using CUIs
     int rel_id = 0;
     try {
        rel_id = editor_kit.insertRelationshipBetweenCUIs("C0000001","C0000002",
          "BT", "mapped_to", "NLM01", "NLM01", "F01-BAC");

     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error inserting relationship (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

     // Insert a relationship using atom ids
     int rel_id = 0;
     try {
        rel_id = editor_kit.processRelationshipBetweenAtoms(12345, 12346,
          "BT", "mapped_to", "NLM01", "NLM01", "F01-BAC");

     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error inserting relationship (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

     // Insert a relationship using atom ids
     int rel_id = 0;
     try {
        rel_id = editor_kit.processRelationshipBetweenConcepts(12345, 12346,
          "BT", "mapped_to", "NLM01", "NLM01", "F01-BAC");

     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error inserting relationship (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

     // Change relationship's tobereleased
     try {
        editor_kit.changeRelationshipTBR(rel_id,"F01-BAC", "n");

     } catch (MEMEException e) {
        System.err.println("Error changing relationship tobereleased value (" +
        e.getMessage() + ")");
     }

   }; // end useEditorKit

 } // end class Test
Each of the methods in this class throws an MEMEException if there is any kind of error. This class no longer directly connects to the database, instead it accesses the MEME application server by extending the standard Client API.

And finally, each of the insertXXX and processXXX methods specify the identifier type in the method name, but in the past the methods insertRelationship() and processRelationship() were overloaded to support both CUIs and atom ids. For backwards compatability we have kept these methods and they still function as they did in the past, however the methods shown in the example above are now preferred.

processRelationshipBetweenCUIs

public int processRelationshipBetweenCUIs(String pr_cui_1,
                                          String pr_cui_2,
                                          String pr_rel_name,
                                          String pr_rel_attr,
                                          String pr_source,
                                          String pr_source_of_label,
                                          String pr_authority,
                                          int pr_rel_id)
                                   throws MEMEException
Modifies or inserts a relationship between CUIs. This method is responsible for taking data from an application and either inserting a new source-level relationship or updating an existing one so its fields match the parameters.

This procedure must "fake" a MOLECULAR_CHANGE_FIELD action by locking max_tab and calling the appropriate series of atomic actions (MEME_APROCS procedures).

It is an update if a source-level relationship match relationship_id. Otherwise, it is an insert if no source-level relationship match relationship_id.

Parameters:
pr_cui_1 - is the possible CUI that this relationship connects.
pr_cui_2 - is the possible CUI that this relationship connects.
pr_rel_name - is the relationship name that should be one of the values returned by getRelationshipNames.
pr_rel_attr - is the relationship attribute that should be one of the values returned by getRelationshipAttributes.
pr_source - is the source asserting the relationship between cui_1 and cui_2.
pr_source_of_label - is the source asserting the nature of the relationship between cui_1 and cui_2.
pr_authority - is the one responsible for the Update/Insert actions.
pr_rel_id - is the ID of the relationships to be processed.
Returns:
relationship_id.
Throws:
MEMEException - if program validation failed.
See Also:
getRelationshipNames(), getRelationshipAttributes()

insertRelationshipBetweenCUIs

public int insertRelationshipBetweenCUIs(String ir_cui_1,
                                         String ir_cui_2,
                                         String ir_rel_name,
                                         String ir_rel_attr,
                                         String ir_source,
                                         String ir_source_of_label,
                                         String ir_authority)
                                  throws MEMEException
Inserts a relationship between two CUIs (SERVER CALL). This method is responsible for taking data from an application and inserting a new source level relationship between cuis.

This procedure must "fake" a MOLECULAR_INSERT action by locking max_tab and calling the appropriate series of atomic actions (MEME_APROCS procedures).

The following defaults are to be assumed for the unspecified relationships fields:

    relationship_level = "S"
    status = "R"
    atom_id_1 = atom_id_2 = 0
    generated = "N"
    dead = "N"
    released = "N"
    tobereleased = "Y"
    suppressible = "N"

Parameters:
ir_cui_1 - is the possible CUI that this relationship connects.
ir_cui_2 - is the possible CUI that this relationship connects.
ir_rel_name - is the relationship name that should be one of the values returned by getRelationshipNames.
ir_rel_attr - is the relationship attribute that should be one of the values returned by getRelationshipAttributes.
ir_source - is the source asserting the relationship between cui_1 and cui_2.
ir_source_of_label - is the source asserting the nature of the relationship between cui_1 and cui_2.
ir_authority - is the one responsible for the Update/Insert actions.

relationship_id.

Inserts a relationship between two concepts (SERVER CALL). This method is responsible for taking data from an application and inserting a new concept level relationship between concepts.

This procedure must "fake" a MOLECULAR_INSERT action by locking max_tab and calling the appropriate series of atomic actions (MEME_APROCS procedures).

The following defaults are to be assumed for the unspecified relationships fields:

    relationship_level = "C"
    status = "R"
    atom_id_1 = 0atom_id_2 = 0
    generated = "N"
    dead = "N"
    released = "N"
    tobereleased = "Y"
    suppressible = "N"

Parameters:

ir_source - is the source asserting the relationship between atom_id_1 and atom_id_2.

changeRelationshipTBR

public void changeRelationshipTBR(int crtbr_rel_id,
                                  String crtbr_authority,
                                  String crtbr_tbr)
                           throws MEMEException
Changes the releasability of an existing relationship (SERVER CALL). This method is responsible for taking data from an application and changing relationship's tobereleased value.

Parameters:

crtbr_authority - is the one responsible for the change actions.
crtbr_tbr - is the new value of tobereleased.
Throws:
